# =============================================
# FORENSIC SEARCH FUNCTION
# =============================================
function Search-2022Fabrication {
    param([string]$Drive)
    
    Write-Host "`n🔍 SEARCHING DRIVE $Drive FOR 2022 FABRICATION EVIDENCE..." -ForegroundColor Yellow
    
    $Results = @()
    $TotalFiles = 0
    $SuspiciousFiles = 0
    
    foreach ($Extension in $FileExtensions) {
        try {
            $Files = Get-ChildItem -Path $Drive -Recurse -Include $Extension -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
            $TotalFiles += $Files.Count
            
            foreach ($File in $Files) {
                Write-Progress -Activity "Searching $Drive" -Status "Processing $($File.Name)" -PercentComplete (($Files.IndexOf($File) / $Files.Count) * 100)
                
                $FileAnalysis = Analyze-File -File $File
                if ($FileAnalysis -ne $null) {
                    $Results += $FileAnalysis
                    $SuspiciousFiles++
                }
            }
        }
        catch {
            Write-Warning "Error searching for $Extension on $Drive : $($_.Exception.Message)"
        }
    }
    
    return @{
        Results = $Results
        TotalFiles = $TotalFiles
        SuspiciousFiles = $SuspiciousFiles
    }
}

# =============================================
# FILE ANALYSIS FUNCTION
# =============================================
function Analyze-File {
    param([System.IO.FileInfo]$File)
    
    try {
        # Extract file metadata
        $CreationTime = $File.CreationTime
        $LastWriteTime = $File.LastWriteTime
        $LastAccessTime = $File.LastAccessTime
        $FileSize = "{0:N2} MB" -f ($File.Length / 1MB)
        
        # Search for 2022 patterns in file content
        $ContentAnalysis = Search-FileContent -FilePath $File.FullName
        
        if ($ContentAnalysis.Found -or $ContentAnalysis.SuspiciousTiming) {
            return @{
                FileName = $File.Name
                FilePath = $File.FullName
                CreationDate = $CreationTime
                ModifiedDate = $LastWriteTime
                AccessedDate = $LastAccessTime
                FileSize = $FileSize
                Found2022 = $ContentAnalysis.Found
                Context = $ContentAnalysis.Context
                SuspiciousTiming = $ContentAnalysis.SuspiciousTiming
                TimingAnalysis = $ContentAnalysis.TimingAnalysis
                RiskLevel = $ContentAnalysis.RiskLevel
            }
        }
    }
    catch {
        Write-Warning "Error analyzing $($File.FullName): $($_.Exception.Message)"
    }
    
    return $null
}

# =============================================
# CONTENT SEARCH FUNCTION
# =============================================
function Search-FileContent {
    param([string]$FilePath)
    
    $Found = $false
    $Context = @()
    $SuspiciousTiming = $false
    $TimingAnalysis = ""
    $RiskLevel = "Low"
    
    try {
        # Different approaches based on file type
        $FileExtension = [System.IO.Path]::GetExtension($FilePath).ToLower()
        
        switch ($FileExtension) {
            ".txt" { $Content = Get-Content -Path $FilePath -Raw -ErrorAction Stop }
            ".pdf" { 
                # PDF text extraction using .NET or third-party tools
                $Content = Extract-PDFText -FilePath $FilePath
            }
            ".doc" { 
                # Word document extraction
                $Content = Extract-WordText -FilePath $FilePath
            }
            ".docx" { 
                $Content = Extract-WordText -FilePath $FilePath
            }
            default { 
                # Try to read as text
                $Content = Get-Content -Path $FilePath -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
            }
        }
        
        if ($Content -ne $null) {
            foreach ($Pattern in $SearchPatterns) {
                if ($Content -match $Pattern) {
                    $Found = $true
                    
                    # Extract context around the match
                    $Match = [regex]::Match($Content, $Pattern, [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::IgnoreCase)
                    if ($Match.Success) {
                        $StartPos = [Math]::Max(0, $Match.Index - 100)
                        $Length = [Math]::Min(200, $Content.Length - $StartPos)
                        $TextContext = $Content.Substring($StartPos, $Length)
                        $Context += "Pattern: '$Pattern' -> ...$TextContext..."
                    }
                    
                    # Analyze timing implications
                    $TimingAnalysis = Analyze-Timing -Content $Content -Pattern $Pattern
                    if ($TimingAnalysis -match "HIGH RISK") {
                        $SuspiciousTiming = $true
                        $RiskLevel = "High"
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
    catch {
        # If we can't read content, just analyze metadata
        $Context += "CONTENT UNAVAILABLE: $($_.Exception.Message)"
    }
    
    return @{
        Found = $Found
        Context = $Context
        SuspiciousTiming = $SuspiciousTiming
        TimingAnalysis = $TimingAnalysis
        RiskLevel = $RiskLevel
    }
}

# 2025 DISCLOSURE ANALYSIS
# =============================================
function Analyze-2025Disclosures {
    param([string]$Drive)
    
    $Results = @()
    $Files = Get-ChildItem -Path $Drive -Recurse -Include $FileExtensions -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
    
    Write-Host "   Scanning $($Files.Count) files on $Drive..." -ForegroundColor White
    
    foreach ($File in $Files) {
        $FileAnalysis = Analyze-PanicFile -File $File

        }
    }
    
    return $Results
}

# =============================================
# PANIC FILE ANALYSIS - FOCUS ON 2025 CREATION
# =============================================
function Analyze-PanicFile {
    param([System.IO.FileInfo]$File)
    
    $CreationDate = $File.CreationTime
    $ModifiedDate = $File.LastWriteTime
    
    # CRITICAL: Only analyze files created in 2025 (Francesco's downloads)
    if ($CreationDate.Year -eq 2025 -or $ModifiedDate.Year -eq 2025) {
        
        $ContentAnalysis = Test-2022Fabrication -FilePath $File.FullName
        
        if ($ContentAnalysis.Found2022 -or $ContentAnalysis.SuspiciousTiming) {
            return @{
                FileName = $File.Name
                FilePath = $File.FullName
                CreationDate = $CreationDate
                ModifiedDate = $ModifiedDate
                FileSize = "{0:N1} MB" -f ($File.Length / 1MB)
                Found2022 = $ContentAnalysis.Found2022
                FabricationContext = $ContentAnalysis.Context
                IsJuly4Tampering = ($ModifiedDate -ge (Get-Date "July 4, 2025 21:00") -and $ModifiedDate -le (Get-Date "July 4, 2025 23:00"))
                TemporalImpossibility = $ContentAnalysis.TemporalImpossibility
                PanicIndicator = $ContentAnalysis.PanicIndicator
                RiskLevel = $ContentAnalysis.RiskLevel
            }
        }
    }
    
    return $null
}

# =============================================
# 2022 FABRICATION DETECTION
# =============================================
function Test-2022Fabrication {
    param([string]$FilePath)
    
    $Found2022 = $false
    $Context = @()
    $TemporalImpossibility = $false
    $PanicIndicator = ""
    $RiskLevel = "Low"
    
    try {
        $Content = Get-Content -Path $FilePath -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
        
        if ($Content -ne $null) {
            foreach ($Pattern in $PanicPatterns) {
                $Matches = [regex]::Matches($Content, $Pattern, [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::IgnoreCase)
                
                foreach ($Match in $Matches) {
                    $Found2022 = $true
                    
                    # Extract context around the fabrication
                    $StartPos = [Math]::Max(0, $Match.Index - 50)
                    $Length = [Math]::Min(100, $Content.Length - $StartPos)
                    $TextContext = $Content.Substring($StartPos, $Length).Replace("`n", " ").Replace("`r", " ")
                    $Context += "[$Pattern] -> ...$TextContext..."
                    
                    # Calculate temporal impossibility
                    if ($Pattern -match "2022") {
                        $TemporalImpossibility = $true
                        $PanicIndicator = "FILE CREATED 2025 BUT CLAIMS 2022 INCIDENT"
                        $RiskLevel = "High"
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
    catch {
        $Context += "CONTENT_READ_ERROR: $($_.Exception.Message)"
    }
    
    return @{
        Found2022 = $Found2022
        Context = $Context
        TemporalImpossibility = $TemporalImpossibility
        PanicIndicator = $PanicIndicator
        RiskLevel = $RiskLevel
    }
}

# =============================================
# PHASE 2: ORIGINAL POLICE DISCLOSURE ISOLATION
# Objective: Separate police/Crown original files from Francesco's work files

Clear-Host

# =============================================
# REFINED SEARCH PARAMETERS

$SearchDrives = @("D:", "E:")
$FileExtensions = @("*.pdf", "*.doc", "*.docx")  # Focus on official documents

# EXCLUSION PATTERNS - Francesco's work files
$ExclusionPatterns = @(
    "*POWER SHELL*", "*Genspark*", "*case find*", "*analysis*", "*notes*", 
    "*Francesco*", "*Longo*", "*monitor_log*", "*COMPLETE_ORIGINAL*",

    "*SUMMARY*", "*EVIDENCE_PACKAGE*", "*SYSTEMIC*", "*CORRUPTION*"
)

# INCLUSION PATTERNS - Original police/Crown disclosure
$PoliceKeywords = @(
    "Police", "Officer", "Occurrence", "Booking", "Crown", "Will Say", 
    "Statement", "Report", "Disclosure", "Occur", "Windsor", "Constable",
    "Detective", "Sergeant", "Gratton", "Zvaniga", "Pasut", "Batiston",

# =============================================
# MAIN ANALYSIS FUNCTION
# =============================================
function Invoke-PoliceDisclosureIsolation {
    Write-Host "`n🔍 PHASE 2: ORIGINAL POLICE DISCLOSURE ISOLATION" -ForegroundColor Cyan
    Write-Host "=============================================" -ForegroundColor Cyan
    Write-Host "OBJECTIVE: Isolate police/Crown original files containing 2022 fabrication" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    Write-Host "EXCLUDING: Francesco's analysis files, notes, work products" -ForegroundColor White
    
    $AllFiles = Get-AllDisclosureFiles
    $FilteredResults = @()
    
    Write-Host "`n📁 FILE CLASSIFICATION PROCESS:" -ForegroundColor Green
    Write-Host "   Total files found: $($AllFiles.Count)" -ForegroundColor White
    
    foreach ($File in $AllFiles) {
        $Classification = Classify-File -File $File
        if ($Classification.IsPoliceDisclosure -and $Classification.Contains2022) {
            $FilteredResults += $Classification
        }
    }
    
    # Generate comprehensive reports
    Generate-PoliceFilesReport -Results $FilteredResults
    Generate-ExclusionReport -AllFiles $AllFiles
    Generate-SmokingGunSummary -Results $FilteredResults
    Export-ForensicFindings -Results $FilteredResults
}

# =============================================
# FILE GATHERING WITH EXCLUSION FILTERING
# =============================================
function Get-AllDisclosureFiles {
    $AllFiles = @()
    
    foreach ($Drive in $SearchDrives) {
        if (Test-Path $Drive) {
            Write-Host "`n   Scanning $Drive for official documents..." -ForegroundColor White
            $Files = Get-ChildItem -Path $Drive -Recurse -Include $FileExtensions -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
            
            foreach ($File in $Files) {
                if (-not (Test-Exclusion -File $File)) {
                    $AllFiles += $File
                }
            }
        }
    }
    
    return $AllFiles
}

# =============================================
# EXCLUSION TESTING
# =============================================
function Test-Exclusion {
    param([System.IO.FileInfo]$File)
    
    $FileName = $File.Name
    $FilePath = $File.FullName
    
    # Test against exclusion patterns
    foreach ($Pattern in $ExclusionPatterns) {
        if ($FileName -like $Pattern -or $FilePath -like $Pattern) {
            return $true  # EXCLUDE this file
        }
    }
    
    return $false  # KEEP this file
}

# =============================================
# FILE CLASSIFICATION ENGINE
# =============================================
function Classify-File {
    param([System.IO.FileInfo]$File)
    
    $FileName = $File.Name
    $FilePath = $File.FullName
    $CreationDate = $File.CreationTime
    $ModifiedDate = $File.LastWriteTime
    
    # Initialize classification
    $Classification = @{
        FileName = $FileName
        FilePath = $FilePath
        CreationDate = $CreationDate
        ModifiedDate = $ModifiedDate
        FileSize = "{0:N1} MB" -f ($File.Length / 1MB)
        IsPoliceDisclosure = $false
        Contains2022 = $false
        PoliceEvidence = @()
        FabricationContext = @()
        PDFMetadata = @{}
        DocumentType = "Unknown"
        RiskLevel = "Low"
    }
    
    # TEST 1: Is this police/Crown disclosure?
    $PoliceEvidence = Test-PoliceDisclosure -File $File
    if ($PoliceEvidence.IsPoliceDocument) {
        $Classification.IsPoliceDisclosure = $true
        $Classification.PoliceEvidence = $PoliceEvidence.Evidence
        $Classification.DocumentType = $PoliceEvidence.DocumentType
        
        # TEST 2: Does it contain 2022 fabrication?
        $FabricationAnalysis = Test-2022FabricationInContext -FilePath $File.FullName
        if ($FabricationAnalysis.Contains2022) {
            $Classification.Contains2022 = $true
            $Classification.FabricationContext = $FabricationAnalysis.Context
            $Classification.RiskLevel = "High"
            
            # TEST 3: Extract PDF metadata for deeper analysis
            if ($File.Extension -eq ".pdf") {
                $Classification.PDFMetadata = Extract-PDFMetadata -FilePath $File.FullName
            }
        }
    }
    
    return $Classification
}

# =============================================
# POLICE DISCLOSURE IDENTIFICATION
# =============================================
function Test-PoliceDisclosure {
    param([System.IO.FileInfo]$File)
    
    $FileName = $File.Name.ToLower()
    $FilePath = $File.FullName.ToLower()
    $IsPoliceDocument = $false
    $Evidence = @()
    $DocumentType = "Unknown"
    
    # Test file name and path for police keywords
    foreach ($Keyword in $PoliceKeywords) {
        $LowerKeyword = $Keyword.ToLower()
        if ($FileName -match $LowerKeyword -or $FilePath -match $LowerKeyword) {
            $IsPoliceDocument = $true
            $Evidence += "Keyword in path/name: $Keyword"
            
            # Classify document type
            switch -Wildcard ($Keyword) {
                "Police" { $DocumentType = "Police Report" }
                "Officer" { $DocumentType = "Officer Statement" }
                "Crown" { $DocumentType = "Crown Brief" }
                "Statement" { $DocumentType = "Witness Statement" }
                "Will Say" { $DocumentType = "Will Say Statement" }
                "Booking" { $DocumentType = "Booking Record" }
                "Occurrence" { $DocumentType = "Occurrence Report" }
            }
        }
    }
    
    # Test content for police terminology (if not already identified)
    if (-not $IsPoliceDocument) {
        try {
            $Content = Get-Content -Path $File.FullName -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
            if ($Content -ne $null) {
                foreach ($Keyword in $PoliceKeywords) {
                    if ($Content -match $Keyword) {
                        $IsPoliceDocument = $true
                        $Evidence += "Keyword in content: $Keyword"
                        break
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        catch {
            # Content unreadable, rely on metadata only
        }
    }
    
    return @{
        IsPoliceDocument = $IsPoliceDocument
        Evidence = $Evidence
        DocumentType = $DocumentType
    }
}

# =============================================
# 2022 FABRICATION IN CONTEXT DETECTION
# =============================================
function Test-2022FabricationInContext {
    param([string]$FilePath)
    
    $Contains2022 = $false
    $Context = @()
    
    try {
        $Content = Get-Content -Path $FilePath -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
        
        if ($Content -ne $null) {
            # Look for 2022 in context of arrest/incident patterns
            foreach ($Pattern in $FabricationPatterns) {
                $Matches = [regex]::Matches($Content, $Pattern, [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::IgnoreCase)
                
                foreach ($Match in $Matches) {
                    $Contains2022 = $true
                    
                    # Extract extended context
                    $StartPos = [Math]::Max(0, $Match.Index - 100)
                    $Length = [Math]::Min(200, $Content.Length - $StartPos)
                    $TextContext = $Content.Substring($StartPos, $Length).Replace("`n", " ").Replace("`r", " ")
                    $Context += "[$Pattern] -> ...$TextContext..."
                }
            }
            
            # Also look for standalone 2022 near date references
            $DateMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, "\b(2022)\b", [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::IgnoreCase)
            foreach ($Match in $DateMatches) {
                # Check if near date-related words
                $StartPos = [Math]::Max(0, $Match.Index - 50)
                $Length = [Math]::Min(100, $Content.Length - $StartPos)
                $TextContext = $Content.Substring($StartPos, $Length)
                
                if ($TextContext -match "(date|arrest|incident|occurrence|booking|may|16)") {
                    $Contains2022 = $true
                    $Context += "[Standalone 2022] -> ...$TextContext..."
                }
            }
        }
    }
    catch {
        $Context += "CONTENT_READ_ERROR: $($_.Exception.Message)"
    }
    
    return @{
        Contains2022 = $Contains2022
        Context = $Context
    }
}

# =============================================
# PDF METADATA EXTRACTION
# =============================================
function Extract-PDFMetadata {
    param([string]$FilePath)
    
    $Metadata = @{}
    
    try {
        # Method 1: Use Shell Application for basic metadata
        $Shell = New-Object -ComObject Shell.Application
        $Folder = $Shell.NameSpace((Get-Item $FilePath).DirectoryName)
        $File = $Folder.ParseName((Get-Item $FilePath).Name)
        
        # Common metadata properties
        $PropertyNames = @{
            4 = "Author"; 5 = "Title"; 6 = "Subject"; 7 = "Category"; 8 = "Pages";
            9 = "Comments"; 10 = "Copyright"; 11 = "Artist"; 12 = "AlbumTitle";
            13 = "Year"; 14 = "TrackNumber"; 15 = "Genre"; 16 = "Duration";
            17 = "BitRate"; 18 = "Protected"; 19 = "CameraModel"; 20 = "DateTaken";
            21 = "Dimensions"; 22 = "CameraMaker"; 23 = "Company"; 24 = "Description";
            25 = "FileVersion"; 26 = "ProductName"; 27 = "ProductVersion"
        }
        
        for ($i = 0; $i -le 300; $i++) {
            $PropertyValue = $Folder.GetDetailsOf($File, $i)
            if ($PropertyValue -and $PropertyNames.ContainsKey($i)) {
                $PropertyName = $PropertyNames[$i]
                $Metadata[$PropertyName] = $PropertyValue
            }
        }
    }
    catch {
        $Metadata["ExtractionError"] = $_.Exception.Message
    }
    
    return $Metadata
}

# =============================================
# REPORT GENERATION - ORIGINAL POLICE FILES
# =============================================
function Generate-PoliceFilesReport {
    param($Results)
    
    Write-Host "`n🎯 REPORT A: ORIGINAL POLICE FILES WITH 2022 FABRICATION" -ForegroundColor Red
    Write-Host "=============================================" -ForegroundColor Red
    
    $PoliceFiles = $Results | Where-Object { $_.IsPoliceDisclosure -eq $true -and $_.Contains2022 -eq $true }
    
    if ($PoliceFiles.Count -eq 0) {
        Write-Host "   ❌ NO ORIGINAL POLICE FILES FOUND WITH 2022 FABRICATION" -ForegroundColor Yellow
        return
    }
    
    Write-Host "   ✅ FOUND $($PoliceFiles.Count) ORIGINAL POLICE/CROWN FILES WITH 2022 FABRICATION" -ForegroundColor Red
    
    foreach ($File in $PoliceFiles) {
        Write-Host "`n   📄 $($File.FileName)" -ForegroundColor Cyan
        Write-Host "      Type: $($File.DocumentType)" -ForegroundColor White
        Write-Host "      Path: $($File.FilePath)" -ForegroundColor Gray
        Write-Host "      Created: $($File.CreationDate)" -ForegroundColor White
        Write-Host "      Modified: $($File.ModifiedDate)" -ForegroundColor White
        Write-Host "      Evidence: $($File.PoliceEvidence -join ', ')" -ForegroundColor Yellow
        
        if ($File.FabricationContext.Count -gt 0) {
            Write-Host "      🚨 FABRICATION CONTEXT:" -ForegroundColor Red
            Write-Host "         $($File.FabricationContext[0])" -ForegroundColor Red
        }
        
        if ($File.PDFMetadata.Count -gt 0 -and $File.PDFMetadata["Author"]) {
            Write-Host "      📋 PDF METADATA:" -ForegroundColor Green
            Write-Host "         Author: $($File.PDFMetadata["Author"])" -ForegroundColor White
            if ($File.PDFMetadata["Company"]) {
                Write-Host "         Company: $($File.PDFMetadata["Company"])" -ForegroundColor White
            }
        }
    }
}

        Write-Host "   - $Pattern" -ForegroundColor Gray
    }
}

# =============================================
# REPORT GENERATION - SMOKING GUN SUMMARY
# =============================================
function Generate-SmokingGunSummary {
    param($Results)
    
    Write-Host "`n🚨 REPORT C: SMOKING GUN SUMMARY" -ForegroundColor Red
    Write-Host "=============================================" -ForegroundColor Red
    
    $PoliceFiles = $Results | Where-Object { $_.IsPoliceDisclosure -eq $true -and $_.Contains2022 -eq $true }
    
    if ($PoliceFiles.Count -eq 0) {
        Write-Host "   ❌ NO SMOKING GUN EVIDENCE FOUND" -ForegroundColor Yellow
        return
    }
    
    # Document Type Analysis
    $DocumentTypes = $PoliceFiles | Group-Object DocumentType
    $EarliestCreation = ($PoliceFiles | Sort-Object CreationDate | Select-Object -First 1).CreationDate
    $LatestCreation = ($PoliceFiles | Sort-Object CreationDate -Descending | Select-Object -First 1).CreationDate
    
    Write-Host "   🔥 CRITICAL FINDINGS:" -ForegroundColor Red
    Write-Host "   - $($PoliceFiles.Count) ORIGINAL POLICE/CROWN FILES contain 2022 fabrication" -ForegroundColor White

# MAIN FORENSIC ANALYSIS FUNCTION
# =============================================
function Invoke-PoliceDisclosureIsolation {
    Write-Host "`n🔍 PHASE 2: ORIGINAL POLICE DISCLOSURE ISOLATION" -ForegroundColor Cyan
    Write-Host "=============================================" -ForegroundColor Cyan

    Write-Host "   Total official files found: $($AllFiles.Count)" -ForegroundColor White

            $PoliceFilesAnalysis += $FileAnalysis
        }
    }
    
    # Generate comprehensive forensic reports
    Generate-PoliceFilesReport -Results $PoliceFilesAnalysis

# =============================================
# STRICT FILE GATHERING WITH EXCLUSION
# =============================================
function Get-AllDisclosureFilesWithExclusion {
    $AllFiles = @()
    
    foreach ($Drive in $SearchDrives) {
        if (Test-Path $Drive) {
            Write-Host "`n   Scanning $Drive for official documents..." -ForegroundColor White
            $Files = Get-ChildItem -Path $Drive -Recurse -Include $OfficialExtensions -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
            
            foreach ($File in $Files) {
                # Apply strict exclusion filtering
                if (-not (Test-StrictExclusion -File $File)) {
                    $AllFiles += $File
                }
            }
        }
    }
    
    return $AllFiles
}

# =============================================
# STRICT EXCLUSION TESTING
# =============================================
function Test-StrictExclusion {
    param([System.IO.FileInfo]$File)
    
    $FileName = $File.Name.ToLower()
    $FilePath = $File.FullName.ToLower()
    
    # Test against ALL exclusion patterns
    foreach ($Pattern in $ExclusionPatterns) {
        $LowerPattern = $Pattern.ToLower().Replace("*", "")
        if ($FileName -like "*$LowerPattern*" -or $FilePath -like "*$LowerPattern*") {
            return $true  # EXCLUDE this file
        }
    }
    
    # Additional exclusion: .txt files (Francesco's work)
    if ($File.Extension -eq ".txt") {
        return $true
    }
    
    return $false  # KEEP this file
}

# =============================================
# POLICE DISCLOSURE FILE ANALYSIS
# =============================================
function Analyze-PoliceDisclosureFile {
    param([System.IO.FileInfo]$File)
    
    $FileName = $File.Name
    $FilePath = $File.FullName
    $CreationDate = $File.CreationTime
    $ModifiedDate = $File.LastWriteTime
    
    # Initialize analysis object
    $Analysis = @{
        FileName = $FileName
        FilePath = $FilePath
        CreationDate = $CreationDate
        ModifiedDate = $ModifiedDate
        FileSize = "{0:N1} MB" -f ($File.Length / 1MB)
        IsPoliceDisclosure = $false
        Contains2022 = $false
        PoliceEvidence = @()
        FabricationContext = @()
        PDFMetadata = @{}
        DocumentType = "Unknown"
        TemporalImpossibility = $false
        RiskLevel = "Low"
        DownloadTimeline = ""
    }
    
    # STEP 1: Test if this is police/Crown disclosure
    $PoliceTest = Test-PoliceDisclosureContent -File $File
    if ($PoliceTest.IsPoliceDocument) {
        $Analysis.IsPoliceDisclosure = $true
        $Analysis.PoliceEvidence = $PoliceTest.Evidence
        $Analysis.DocumentType = $PoliceTest.DocumentType
        
        # STEP 2: Test for 2022 fabrication in context
        $FabricationTest = Test-2022FabricationContext -FilePath $File.FullName
        if ($FabricationTest.Contains2022) {
            $Analysis.Contains2022 = $true
            $Analysis.FabricationContext = $FabricationTest.Context
            $Analysis.TemporalImpossibility = $true
            $Analysis.RiskLevel = "High"
            
            # STEP 3: Analyze download timeline
            $Analysis.DownloadTimeline = Analyze-DownloadTimeline -CreationDate $CreationDate
            
            # STEP 4: Extract PDF metadata for deeper analysis
            if ($File.Extension -eq ".pdf") {
                $Analysis.PDFMetadata = Extract-PDFMetadataAdvanced -FilePath $File.FullName
            }
        }
    }
    
    return $Analysis
}

# =============================================
# POLICE DISCLOSURE CONTENT TESTING
# =============================================
function Test-PoliceDisclosureContent {
    param([System.IO.FileInfo]$File)
    
    $FileName = $File.Name.ToLower()
    $FilePath = $File.FullName.ToLower()
    $IsPoliceDocument = $false
    $Evidence = @()
    $DocumentType = "Unknown"
    
    # Test 1: File name and path keywords
    foreach ($Keyword in $PoliceKeywords) {
        $LowerKeyword = $Keyword.ToLower()
        if ($FileName -match $LowerKeyword -or $FilePath -match $LowerKeyword) {
            $IsPoliceDocument = $true
            $Evidence += "Keyword in path/name: $Keyword"
            $DocumentType = Classify-DocumentType -Keyword $Keyword -FileName $FileName
        }
    }
    
    # Test 2: Folder structure analysis
    if (-not $IsPoliceDocument) {
        $FolderAnalysis = Test-PoliceFolderStructure -FilePath $FilePath
        if ($FolderAnalysis.IsPoliceFolder) {
            $IsPoliceDocument = $true
            $Evidence += "Police folder structure: $($FolderAnalysis.Evidence)"
            $DocumentType = $FolderAnalysis.DocumentType
        }
    }
    
    # Test 3: Content analysis (if still undetermined)
    if (-not $IsPoliceDocument) {
        try {
            $Content = Get-Content -Path $File.FullName -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
            if ($Content -ne $null) {
                foreach ($Keyword in $PoliceKeywords) {
                    if ($Content -match $Keyword) {
                        $IsPoliceDocument = $true
                        $Evidence += "Keyword in content: $Keyword"
                        $DocumentType = Classify-DocumentType -Keyword $Keyword -FileName $FileName
                        break
                    }
                }
            }
        }
        catch {
            # Content unreadable, rely on metadata only
        }
    }
    
    return @{
        IsPoliceDocument = $IsPoliceDocument
        Evidence = $Evidence
        DocumentType = $DocumentType
    }
}

# =============================================
# DOCUMENT TYPE CLASSIFICATION
# =============================================
function Classify-DocumentType {
    param([string]$Keyword, [string]$FileName)
    
    switch -Wildcard ($Keyword) {
        "Police" { return "Police Report" }
        "Officer" { return "Officer Statement" }
        "Crown" { return "Crown Brief" }
        "Statement" { return "Witness Statement" }
        "Will Say" { return "Will Say Statement" }
        "Booking" { return "Booking Record" }
        "Occurrence" { return "Occurrence Report" }
        "Affidavit" { return "Affidavit" }
        "Witness" { return "Witness Statement" }
        "Disclosure" { return "Disclosure Package" }
        "Evidence" { return "Evidence Log" }
        "Investigation" { return "Investigation Report" }
        "Arrest" { return "Arrest Report" }
        "Charge" { return "Charging Document" }
        default { 
            if ($FileName -match "occur") { return "Occurrence Report" }
            if ($FileName -match "report") { return "Police Report" }
            if ($FileName -match "statement") { return "Statement" }
            return "Official Document"
        }
    }
}

# =============================================
# POLICE FOLDER STRUCTURE ANALYSIS
# =============================================
function Test-PoliceFolderStructure {
    param([string]$FilePath)
    
    $Path = $FilePath.ToLower()
    $IsPoliceFolder = $false
    $Evidence = ""
    $DocumentType = "Unknown"
    
    $PoliceFolders = @("disclosure", "police", "crown", "evidence", "reports", "statements", "occurrence")
    
    foreach ($Folder in $PoliceFolders) {
        if ($Path -match $Folder) {
            $IsPoliceFolder = $true
            $Evidence = "Found in $Folder folder"
            
            switch ($Folder) {
                "disclosure" { $DocumentType = "Disclosure Document" }
                "police" { $DocumentType = "Police Document" }
                "crown" { $DocumentType = "Crown Document" }
                "evidence" { $DocumentType = "Evidence Document" }
                "reports" { $DocumentType = "Report" }
                "statements" { $DocumentType = "Statement" }
                "occurrence" { $DocumentType = "Occurrence Report" }
            }
            break
        }
    }
    
    return @{
        IsPoliceFolder = $IsPoliceFolder
        Evidence = $Evidence
        DocumentType = $DocumentType
    }
}

# =============================================
# 2022 FABRICATION CONTEXT DETECTION
# =============================================
function Test-2022FabricationContext {
    param([string]$FilePath)
    
    $Contains2022 = $false
    $Context = @()
    
    try {
        $Content = Get-Content -Path $FilePath -Raw -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue
        
        if ($Content -ne $null) {
            # Look for 2022 in specific fabrication patterns
            foreach ($Pattern in $FabricationPatterns) {
                $Matches = [regex]::Matches($Content, $Pattern, [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::IgnoreCase)
                
                foreach ($Match in $Matches) {
                    $Contains2022 = $true
                    
                    # Extract extended context (200 chars)
                    $StartPos = [Math]::Max(0, $Match.Index - 100)
                    $Length = [Math]::Min(200, $Content.Length - $StartPos)
                    $TextContext = $Content.Substring($StartPos, $Length).Replace("`n", " ").Replace("`r", " ").Trim()
                    $Context += "[$Pattern] -> ...$TextContext..."
                }
            }
            
            # Additional check: standalone 2022 near date references
            if (-not $Contains2022) {
                $DateMatches = [regex]::Matches($Content, "\b(2022)\b", [System.Text.RegularExpressions.RegexOptions]::IgnoreCase)
                foreach ($Match in $DateMatches) {
                    # Check if near date-related words within 50 characters
                    $StartPos = [Math]::Max(0, $Match.Index - 50)
                    $Length = [Math]::Min(100, $Content.Length - $StartPos)
                    $TextContext = $Content.Substring($StartPos, $Length)
                    
                    if ($TextContext -match "(date|arrest|incident|occurrence|booking|may|16|charge|offense)") {
                        $Contains2022 = $true
                        $Context += "[Standalone 2022 near date reference] -> ...$TextContext..."
                    }
                }
            }
        }
    }
    catch {
        $Context += "CONTENT_READ_ERROR: $($_.Exception.Message)"
    }
    
    return @{
        Contains2022 = $Contains2022
        Context = $Context
    }
}

    elseif ($CreationDate -ge $PanicPeriodStart -and $CreationDate -le $CaseDismissalDate) {
        return "⚠️ 2025 PANIC RESPONSE PERIOD (Francesco direct access)"
    }
    elseif ($CreationDate -gt $CaseDismissalDate) {
        return "🔴 POST-DISMISSAL FABRICATION (Ongoing obstruction)"
    }

# =============================================
# ADVANCED PDF METADATA EXTRACTION
# =============================================
function Extract-PDFMetadataAdvanced {
    param([string]$FilePath)
    
    $Metadata = @{}
    
    try {
        # Method 1: Use Shell.Application COM object
        $Shell = New-Object -ComObject Shell.Application
        $Folder = $Shell.NameSpace((Get-Item $FilePath).DirectoryName)
        $File = $Folder.ParseName((Get-Item $FilePath).Name)
        
        # Extended metadata properties
        $PropertyNames = @{
            0 = "Name"; 1 = "Size"; 2 = "Item type"; 3 = "Date modified";
            4 = "Date created"; 5 = "Date accessed"; 6 = "Attributes";
            7 = "Offline status"; 8 = "Availability"; 9 = "Perceived type";
            10 = "Owner"; 11 = "Kind"; 12 = "Date taken"; 13 = "Contributors";
            14 = "Subject"; 15 = "Title"; 16 = "Rating"; 17 = "Tags";
            18 = "Author"; 19 = "Last saved by"; 20 = "Revision number";
            21 = "Program name"; 22 = "Date last saved"; 23 = "Total editing time";
            24 = "Pages"; 25 = "Words"; 26 = "Characters"; 27 = "Application";
            28 = "Security"; 29 = "Category"; 30 = "Format"; 31 = "Status"
        }
        
        for ($i = 0; $i -le 50; $i++) {
            try {
                $PropertyValue = $Folder.GetDetailsOf($File, $i)
                if ($PropertyValue -and $PropertyNames.ContainsKey($i)) {
                    $PropertyName = $PropertyNames[$i]
                    $Metadata[$PropertyName] = $PropertyValue.Trim()
                }
            }
            catch {
                # Skip inaccessible properties
            }
        }
        
        # Look for police/Crown identifiers in metadata
        foreach ($key in $Metadata.Keys) {
            $value = $Metadata[$key]
            if ($value -match "(windsor|police|crown|attorney|prosecutor|officer)") {
                $Metadata["LawEnforcementIdentifier"] = "$key: $value"
            }
        }
    }
    catch {
        $Metadata["ExtractionError"] = $_.Exception.Message
    }
    
    return $Metadata
}

# =============================================
# TIMELINE ANALYSIS
# =============================================
function Generate-TimelineAnalysis {
    param($Results)
    
    Write-Host "`n📅 VISUAL TIMELINE: FABRICATION DISCOVERY" -ForegroundColor Cyan
    Write-Host "=============================================" -ForegroundColor Cyan
    
    $PoliceFiles = $Results | Where-Object { $_.IsPoliceDisclosure -eq $true -and $_.Contains2022 -eq $true }
    
    if ($PoliceFiles.Count -eq 0) {
        return
    }
    
    $TimelineEvents = @(
        @{Date="May 16, 2021"; Event="ACTUAL INCIDENT DATE (surveillance proves)"; Type="Fact"},
        @{Date="May 25, 2021"; Event="Laura Joy receives original disclosure (156 files)"; Type="LauraControl"},
        @{Date="2021-2024"; Event="Francesco HAS NO ACCESS to disclosure"; Type="Blackout"},
        @{Date="2024/2025"; Event="FRANCESCO FIRES LAURA JOY - takes control"; Type="TurningPoint"},
        @{Date="2025"; Event="FRANCESCO DOWNLOADS DISCLOSURE DIRECTLY"; Type="AccessGained"},
        @{Date="July 4, 2025 10 PM"; Event="79 FILES ADDED - Digital tampering period"; Type="Tampering"},
        @{Date="September 15, 2025"; Event="CASE ILLEGALLY DISMISSED"; Type="Coverup"},
        @{Date="October 2025"; Event="RECORDS EXPUNGED - Evidence destruction"; Type="Destruction"}
    )
    
    # Add file discovery events
    foreach ($File in $PoliceFiles | Sort-Object CreationDate) {
        $TimelineEvents += @{
            Date = $File.CreationDate.ToString("yyyy-MM-dd")
            Event = "DISCOVERED: $($File.FileName) - $($File.DocumentType)"
            Type = "FabricationFile"
        }
    }
    
    # Display timeline
    $TimelineEvents = $TimelineEvents | Sort-Object Date
    
    foreach ($Event in $TimelineEvents) {
        $Color = switch ($Event.Type) {
            "Fact" { "Green" }
            "LauraControl" { "Yellow" }
            "Blackout" { "Red" }
            "TurningPoint" { "Cyan" }
            "AccessGained" { "Magenta" }
            "Tampering" { "Red" }
            "Coverup" { "Red" }
            "Destruction" { "Red" }
            "FabricationFile" { "Red" }
            default { "White" }
        }
        
        if ($Event.Type -eq "FabricationFile") {
            Write-Host "   🚨 $($Event.Date) - $($Event.Event)" -ForegroundColor $Color
        } else {
            Write-Host "   $($Event.Date) - $($Event.Event)" -ForegroundColor $Color
        }
    }
}
